<p>This page's history is somewhat of a big mess, I must admit. There are a lot of insane things that happened because of my recklessness. I'm not super proud of the many really stupid things I did during this time.</p>
<p>From filling up the wiki's image files with my art, to filling up the page with art to the point where people couldn't access my page without their phones or computers crashing, it was an incredible mess that I still get embarrassed about.</p>
<p>A lot of people had to help me out during this time, and I feel really bad for the people who had to stare at my old art for hours fixing up the mistakes I made on my page.</p>
<p>My art on this page is very messy, especially in the first few pages. I loved drawing, but I feel that I rushed a lot of the drawings on this page, because I wanted to draw things so badly. I should've taken my time with some of the things I drew on here, but then again, I was a very excitable person who wanted to tackle millions of things.</p>
<p>A lot of people supported me during the time I first began drawing, which, honestly, I am very surprised to this day, and I am forever thankful for.</p>
<p>I ended up drawing 6 things a day. That took a toll on me! It most definitely wasn't a good idea! I suffered two art crashes during this time, and I took breaks for each of those crashes. You should always take breaks if you crash, I feel.</p>
<p>I do love some of the things I drew on here, but most of it is very messy and if you want to look into my art, I do not recommend starting with this page unless you're interested in seeing my older work. Also, be warned, some of the SCPs might be outdated since this was probably a year ago or more.</p>
<p>I have a knack for drawing International SCPs that I still sometimes do to this day. International SCPs are all so interesting cause they all come from different perspectives of people, and it's so interesting to see the SCPs they write. A few International SCPs have become some of my all time favorites! So thank you, INT community, for being awesome.</p>
<p>Page Theme: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wPo2vYTldY8">Coc'n Rolla</a></p>
<p>Translations: This page is pretty much impossible to translate, but the text isn't really important in the first place, it's usually just shitposting. Anyone can enjoy it no matter what language branch.</p>
</div>
