<p>This was when I started to slow my roll, I decided instead of 6 a day, I would do only 2 a day. I also made a lot of changes to my art style. I still kept the cartoony stick figure style from my earlier drawings of course, but there are a lot of differences.</p>
<p>Some of these include:</p>
<p>1. No black outlines on the characters.<br />
2. Thicker limbs.<br />
3. More taking advantage of textures and effects on my program.<br />
4. A better ability to tackle SCPs that I thought I'd never be able to draw.<br />
5. More use of the shape tools that were added to my program.</p>
<p><a href="https://i.imgur.com/OJO4dG7.png">Example.</a></p>
<p>Do I think my art is perfect? Of course not. However, I do feel I really improved and it's made me feel very great.</p>
<p>I very much recommend this page for those interested in my art. Seriously, I had so much fun working on the art for this page, even the stuff I think I could have done better on I still look back on fondly.</p>
<p>I have taken a break from posting on it indefinitely, but that hasn't stopped me from drawing art during this time, so I might upload more some day.</p>
<p>Page Theme: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wnQf_5k2CUc">そこにはまた迷宮</a></p>
<p>Translations: Again, no translations, but the <a href="http://scpfoundation.net/artwork:pastarasta1">Russian branch</a> did a collection of drawings I did of their SCPs.</p>
<p>Thanks a bunch! I am a huge fan of -RU SCPs because some of them give me a real &quot;good and classic SCP&quot; feel. Also, Arbelict is an awesome writer and deserves more translations of their work.</p>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-3" style="display:none">
