</div>
<p>I am honestly incredibly surprised at the amount of people that like this Parawatch article. As of writing this is the most well rated tale of this month, and it was posted during the rating period of the Mystery Contest.</p>
<p>Parawatch has got to be one of my favorite new GOIs on this site, simply because of the many opportunities it has given to writers on this site.</p>
<p>Ever since writing this, I've wanted to make more creepypasta referencing SCPs/tales. I feel like this is an untapped market. Not like there haven't been creepypasta referencing SCPs/tales before, though.</p>
<p>I always wanted to make an established character in the SCP Wiki, and I think michael was a success. I don't expect it to have a huge fan following or a bunch of stories being made about him any time soon, but I'm really, really happy that I was able to bring this metafictional child ghost to life.</p>
<p>michael is based off, obviously, by Jeff the Killer. The child ghost angle was also inspired by BEN Drowned. I want to do more with this creepypasta theme I gave to michael, so maybe someday I will write another tale about him. I don't think I could write another Parawatch starring him though, I rather write a creepypasta for my next Parawatch. Perhaps something to do with a video game, I donno.</p>
<p>A few people have said this story has creeped them out. I am very surprised considering the story is a lot more funny to me then it is scary. I did write it with the intent of a mix of horror and humor, but I think I did more humor than horror, personally.</p>
<p>Thanks so much to everyone who read this. I'm really happy you took the time to read and decide if you liked it or not. It means the absolute world to me.</p>
<p>Page Theme: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FeMFSOkNoSQ">Roblox Haunted House Music</a></p>
<p>Translations: <a href="http://scp-wiki-cn.wikidot.com/michael-the-kiler">Chinese Branch</a> translated my story, which I am incredibly grateful for. I am very perplexed at how quickly this translation was done, considering the broken english in which michael speaks in.</p>
<p><a href="http://scpfoundation.net/michael-the-kiler">Russian Branch</a> has also done a translation, thanks a bunch!</p>
</div>
