<p><strong>Lost Footage Found Episode</strong> is a blog I made a while ago that's basically about the odd aesthetics of internet horror, and horror in general. It's slightly personal. The title is a mix of &quot;lost episode&quot; and &quot;found footage&quot;.</p>
<p>It's a mix of aesthetic posts, posts about horror I love, screenshots from stories, and posts about stuff that I find humorous or odd about the horror from my past and the horror of today.</p>
<p>It's basically just a big love letter to horror in general, but the basic theming is creepypasta and the SCP Wiki, as it played a very big part of my life when I was getting into the horror genre.</p>
<p>This blog was very inspired by blogs such as <a href="https://realfootage.tumblr.com/">realfootage</a> and <a href="https://scarymario.tumblr.com/">scarymario.</a> As well as a bit of <a href="https://twitter.com/scp_txt?lang=en">scp.txt.</a></p>
<p>The offical SCP Wiki blog (as well as some friends) sometimes reblog my aesthetic posts and SCP posts, which is very nice of them, thanks! I appreciate it a lot.</p>
<p>I am planning on doing a lot more with this blog soon, make readings, some art, maybe even make a website. Who knows where I'll go with this.</p>
<p>I will make a note, most of the stuff on this blog is not made by me, as this is more of a &quot;stuff i remember and stuff i like&quot; blog. I source art that I post, and I source stories when asked. I'll also remove posts if people related to the creation of what I'm posting ask.</p>
<p>Page Theme: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6LB7LZZGpkw">Theme of Laura</a></p>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-6" style="display:none">
<p>This is a collection of SCPs I absolutely have fallen in love with. Also some tales. I'll update this list more and more, because my memory can fail me.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-2747">SCP-2747</a> is a SCP that I would say is a perfect blend of lost media horror and meta SCP horror. There's something so goddamn sinister about the anafabula and I love it so much! I'm surprised the author wasn't familiar with Killswitch when they wrote it, cause it reminded me of that so much!</p>
<p><a href="/scp-3012">SCP-3012</a> is one of my favorite GAW articles on this site. It's incredibly rich in character, and the anomaly is very enjoyable to me. I recommend.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-261">SCP-261!</a> An absolute classic! If you haven't read this yet, what are you doing!? It's super fun! If you like the concept of alien or anomalous food, this SCP will be right up your ally.</p>
<p>No wonder <a href="http://scp-int.wikidot.com/scp-280-jp">SCP-280-JP</a> is the most upvoted -JP article on the SCP-JP Wiki. It's super well done. A concept that seems so simple, yet creative, done in an interesting and awesome way!</p>
<p><a href="/critter-profile-bakugo">Critter Profile: Bakugo!</a> is a really great WWS entry, which, as a GOI, is really fun to me, as I love anomalous animals. This entry was an incredibly enjoyable one! Also, the tapir is cute.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-3896">SCP-3896</a> is probably one of the most underrated SCPs I have ever read. I am soooo into everything about this SCP and I'd love to see more art of it someday. I'll never stop eating Big Gordo.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-4240">SCP-4240</a> is such an awesome love letter to ritual creepypasta. Did I mention how much I'm into ritual stories in the first place? Especially ones about going into different dimensions or summoning creatures. This SCP does a great job at replicating the feeling of reading one, while adding a little twist to the mix.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-3335">SCP-3335</a> is just super crazy. I've always been a fan of anomalous drugs that do weird things to peoples bodies, and this was no different. Some of the body horror in this feels so simple yet so wrong and nasty. I super recommend for people who like rlly gross horror.</p>
</div>
