<p>This is where I put my future SCP/Tale ideas so I don't forget them</p>
<p>- Anger management that <em>really</em> lets it all out.</p>
<p>- Imposter challenge idea: A Five Guys building that can be consumed, but only if you earnestly wanted to eat it. Meant to emulate a <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=617958&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609987824" alt="Communism will win" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=617958)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;">Communism will win</a></span> article.</p>
<p>- A waterslide that takes people to a dimension of which is an infinite, spiraling, shapeshifting waterslide. It release those into the pool it is connected to once they're scared to the point of a panic attack. It does not harm those inside, deliberately protecting them if they are ever in danger during the ride.</p>
<p>- Cartoon show in which the characters are severally affected by fanart and the love/hate it gets.</p>
<p>- Noise album that fucks your shit up.</p>
<p>- Weird, chalk white creatures that dig up corpses and dance with them.</p>
<p>- The Foundation would uncover this bizarre cloning facility underground their regular facility, and it's all for this one D-Class, D-1711. They then find out that this D-Class has been used a bunch of times without them even knowing. Also, it's not even like, made out of human shit, it's a weird spongy biomass that takes the shape of a human.</p>
<p>- Inspired by a conversation I had with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kinchtheknifeblade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1345012); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1345012&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609987824" alt="kinchtheknifeblade" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1345012)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kinchtheknifeblade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1345012); return false;">kinchtheknifeblade</a></span>. A Parawatch tale about a lost episode of Sheep in the Big City, implied to be a continuation of the ending for the first season (in which the sheep was revealed to be evil). Throw in a bunch of unsettling imagery without it being overtly gory or stupid.</p>
<p>- Website that catalogs &quot;Fast Food Critters&quot;, feral creatures that feast only upon the food of whatever fast food restaurant they're made for. There is only one for each restaurant. These creatures didn't exist until the website was created.</p>
